@node wcslen
@section @code{wcslen}---get wide-character string length 
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <wchar.h>
size_t wcslen(const wchar_t *@var{s});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
The @code{wcslen} function computes the number of wide-character codes
in the wide-character string to which @var{s} points, not including the
terminating null wide-character code.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
The @code{wcslen} function returns the length of @var{s}; no return value is
reserved to indicate an error.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{wcslen} is ISO/IEC 9899/AMD1:1995 (ISO C).

No supporting OS subroutines are required.

@*
